# Platform Profile: ChatGPT / OpenAI

**Provider:** OpenAI  
**Current Flagship:** GPT-5.4 / GPT-5.5  
**Interface:** chatgpt.com, API, enterprise deployments

---

## Strengths
- Best all-rounder — strongest breadth across task types of any platform
- Largest tool ecosystem: web search, code execution, image generation, file analysis, computer use
- Agentic computer use — can operate desktop environments and complete long-horizon tasks
- Multimodal: strong image, audio, and document understanding
- GPT-5.5 leads on complex debugging and large-codebase reasoning
- 1M token context window (API)
- Enterprise deployment maturity — ChatGPT Enterprise is widely adopted
- Strong for business document production (presentations, spreadsheets, legal/financial analysis)
- Codex integration for coding tasks

## Weaknesses
- Prose quality slightly below Claude for long-form writing
- Can be verbose — responses sometimes pad beyond what's needed
- Less precise at following highly detailed, structured instructions than Claude
- Custom GPTs and memory features are consumer-grade; enterprise memory is limited

## Context Window
- GPT-5.4: 1M tokens (API)
- chatgpt.com: 128K effective in standard chat
- Behavior: Strong at large context; some degradation at extreme lengths

## Memory & Persistence
- **Memory feature:** Learns from conversations over time (consumer accounts)
- **Custom Instructions:** Persistent preferences and context across sessions
- **Projects:** Persistent file and context storage within a project
- **ChatGPT Enterprise:** Org-level memory and data governance controls
- **Handoff note:** Custom Instructions or a project system prompt are the most reliable persistence surfaces

## System Prompt Support
- ✅ Full system prompt support via API
- ✅ Custom Instructions function as a persistent system prompt in chatgpt.com
- ✅ GPTs (custom deployments) support full system prompts

## Tool Availability
- Web search (native)
- Code execution (Python sandbox — native)
- Image generation (DALL-E integration)
- File upload and analysis (PDF, Excel, CSV, images)
- Computer use (desktop automation — GPT-5.4+)
- Plugin/tool ecosystem (extensive)
- API tool calling / function calling

## Prompt Format Conventions
- Responds well to direct, conversational prompts as well as structured ones
- Markdown formatting in prompts is interpreted and mirrored in output
- System prompts should establish role, context, and behavioral constraints
- Benefits from explicit output format specification
- Handles very long prompts but may summarize or compress heavily structured content

## Ideal Task Types
- Multimodal tasks (image + text reasoning)
- Business document generation (presentations, reports, financial models)
- Broad research where web access + synthesis are both needed
- Agentic computer use tasks (filling forms, operating software)
- Code generation with execution and validation
- Enterprise knowledge work across diverse formats
- Tasks requiring the widest available toolset

